m Planck}'s cosmological measurements of the\nprimary Cosmic Microwave Background (CMB). Given the \\textit{Planck} cluster\nmasses, if an (unlikely) uncorrected $\\sim 20$ % calibration bias existed, this\ntension would be eased, but not resolved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 Aug 2014 18:53:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 Jan 2015 19:52:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-22"}
